  "text": "Cell lines. Human metaphase spreads were obtained from PHAstimulated peripheral blood lymphocytes of a normal human donor. Cell lines from primates have been previously reported [CITATION_1] . Five primate species were used in this study: HSA (Homo sapiens); three great apes: common chimpanzee Pan troglodytes (PTR), gorilla Gorilla gorilla (GGO) and orang utan Pongo pygmaeus (PPY); and the Black Lemur Eulemur macaco (EMA).",
